>:</span></p><blockquote><p>=E2=80=9CIn yet another surreal moment, I recei=
ved notification that my application for a Gates Cambridge scholarship to s=
tudy for a doctorate at the University of Cambridge was successful. With a =
1.3 percent acceptance rate, obtaining the scholarship was even more unlike=
ly than getting into Yale. Applicants had to demonstrate academic excellenc=
e, leadership ability, and a commitment to improving the lives of others. B=
etween my college transcript, military experience, and my unusual upbringin=
g, I figured I=E2=80=99d be competitive, but I was far from confident. Now,=
 I couldn=E2=80=99t believe I was going back across the Atlantic yet again.=
=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p><span>After </span><a href=3D"https://www.robk=
henderson.com/p/five-winters-in-cambridge" rel=3D"">6 years of living in th=
e UK</a><span>, I=E2=80=99m returning to the US.</span></p><p>I arrive in N=
ew York City tomorrow, October 16. I=E2=80=99ll be apartment hunting during=
 the next few weeks.</p><p>If you happen to have a nice place you=E2=80=99r=
e renting out and want to offer a discounted rate to provide shelter to a h=
alf-Latinx half-Asian former foster child of color, you will singlehandedly=
 advance the cause of social justice.</p><p>For the New Yorkers among you=
=E2=80=94transplants, natives, and those who are familiar with the city=E2=
=80=94please hit me with any helpful comments, tips, guidance, etc.</p><p>Y=
ou can respond directly to this email or in the comments section below.</p>=
<div><hr></div><p>There are plenty of opportunities I=E2=80=99ll be explori=
ng while living in New York City, including a potential podcast miniseries =
I=E2=80=99m excited about.</p><p><span>Ordinarily, for a relatively young w=
riter who doesn=E2=80=99t have rich parents, moving to New York City would =
be financially unwise. But I=E2=80=99m able to make this transition because=
 of your support. My readers. I=E2=80=99ll never fail to remember that. By =
the way, now=E2=80=99s a good time to remind those of you who aren=E2=80=99=
t yet paid subscribers that there are more than </span><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.robkhenderson.com/archive" rel=3D"">100 premium posts in the archive</a>=
<span>. Paid subscribers also get access to regular Ask Me Anything threads=
, along with my livestreams where you can ask me anything you want. And ste=
ep discounts for 1-on-1 video meetings with me. </span></p><p>Here are some=
 recent paid subscriber-only essays that readers have enjoyed:</p><ul><li><=
p><a href=3D"https://www.robkhenderson.com/p/yes-elites-have-always-been-hy=
pocrites" rel=3D"">The Hypocrisy of the New Upper Class</a></p></li><li><p>=
